  - Running automated tests to verify the code quality. âœ…

2. Testing Phase ğŸ§ª

- Continuous Testing: Automated testing of the application in different environments to ensure it meets the required standards. ğŸŒ
- Tools: Selenium, JUnit, TestNG. ğŸ› ï¸
- Practices:
  - Integration of testing scripts with CI tools. ğŸ”„
  - Running tests automatically after each code integration. ğŸš€

3. Deployment Phase ğŸš€

- Continuous Deployment (CD): Automatically deploying every change that passes the tests to production. ğŸŒ
- Continuous Delivery: Ensuring that the code is always in a deployable state. ğŸŸ¢
- Tools: Docker, Kubernetes, Ansible, Terraform. ğŸ› ï¸
- Practices:
  - Automating deployment scripts. ğŸ“
